Testing the ASE score for the available predictors

# set up the initial ASE feed
reg.fwd=regsubsets(registered~humidity + windspeed + temp + atemp + weather  + workingday + holiday + season + casual ,data=bike_train,method="forward",nvmax=9)

# Test ASE prediction
predict.regsubsets =function (object , newdata ,id ,...){
  form=as.formula (object$call [[2]])
  mat=model.matrix(form ,newdata )
  coefi=coef(object ,id=id)
  xvars=names(coefi)
  mat[,xvars]%*%coefi
}

testASE<-c()
for (i in 1:9){
  predictions<-predict.regsubsets(object=reg.fwd,newdata=bike_train,id=i) 
  testASE[i]<-mean(bike_train$registered-predictions)
}

testASE
## [1]  1.991045e-13 -8.972678e-14  1.087344e-13  2.243210e-13  2.167275e-13
## [6]  2.113829e-13  1.462412e-13  2.787978e-14  2.552273e-14
# plot the ASE model
par(mfrow=c(1,1))
plot(1:9,testASE,type="l",xlab="# of predictors",ylab="test vs train ASE")
index<-which(testASE==min(testASE))
points(index,testASE[index],col="red",pch=10)
rss<-summary(reg.fwd)$rss
lines(1:9,rss/10886,lty=3,col="blue")  # Dividing by 10886 since ASE=RSS/sample size

# build the model for scoring
model.base.formula = count ~ weather + 
                             windspeed + 
                             atemp +
                             weather +
                             workingday + 
                             holiday +
                             season

# store the model for scoring
model  <- lm(formula = model.base.formula, data = bike_train)
                            
# apply the model to the test data set                             
bike_test$count <- predict.lm(model, bike_test)
